12/04/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Eleven people, including three German students on holiday, died in the Mediterranean resort of Kemer after they drank spirits bought on the black market, the agriculture ministry announced on Saturday (April 11th).
This is the second tragedy involving methyl alcohol poisoning in Turkey in the past four years.
In 2005, 20 people died after they consumed dangerous spirits.
(Reuters, BTA, AFP, RIA Novosti, DPA - 11/04/09)
